EQ checks every time an attack is made with a weapon to see if the skill in that weapon type ups.  So, the faster the weapon the more swings you get, and therefore the more chances for a skill increase.  Thus to practice a weapon skill you want as low a delay as possible for practice a 1/20 weapon is far superior to a 70/40 weapon. ( mind you when push comes to shove you want the 70/40 weilded NOW.) <br>
<br>
The hand a weaopn is in does not matter, if you can attack with a heand you cna get skill ups with that hand.  Mind you since the primary hand attacks at least 2X and in the begining, more like 10X as fast as the secondary hand you will get far more practice with the primary hand weapon.  Ideally you weild 2 weapons of the apropriate type ( faster weapon in primary hand), next most preferable is ( primary hand, other type in secondary -- you can and will get some increases in both types , but offhand weapon wil advance SLOOOOOWLY.  ) <br>
